            <thetext>The GalleryList computes the width of the galleryText div thusly:

text.style.width=(this.getWidth()-100-this.getThumbMaxWidth())+&quot;px&quot;;

This is fine if you&#39;re using the default stylesheet.  But if you have customized it to pack more information into the cell, you end up wasting about 70 pixels of usable space, with no way to override it in the stylesheet.

This should be a public property that can be set (it can default to the computed value if no explicit value is set).</thetext>
